com.navis.framework.portal.cache

Class AbstractEntityCacheConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.navis.external.framework.AbstractExtensionCallback
      • com.navis.framework.portal.cache.AbstractEntityCacheConfiguration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EExtensionCallback, IEntityCacheConfiguration
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArgoAbstractEntityCacheConfiguration

    public abstract class AbstractEntityCacheConfiguration
extends AbstractExtensionCallback
implements IEntityCacheConfiguration
    This class is the superclass of all the cache metafield providers. An entity cache metafield provider provides: 1. A list of entity metafields which need to be cached. 2. A list of related entities as well as their metafields which need to be added to cache. They can be direct relations (foreign keys in entity to be cached) or any related entity which is navigable from the current entity. 3. For fields from other entities it provides the fully qualified fields. 4. Common methods to create domain queries and fetch values of entities which is used during initial building of cache as well as during insert processing of cached entities
    Author:
    Arvinder Brar, 2016-01-29

        Specified by:
        getQualifiedMetafieldIds in interface IEntityCacheConfiguration
        Parameters:
        inMetafieldId - metafield id
        inBaseEntity - cached entity name
        inEntityOfField - entity to which the field belongs
        Returns:
        list of qualified metafield id with navigation path from cached entity name to the updated entity name. In most cases a single metafield will be returned. A list is only returned if one entity has multiple foreign key fields pointing to same entity, for example, WorkInstruction entity has multiple fields which hold reference to Che entity (WI_ITV, WI_CHE and so on) A field will only be added to the returned list if it is one of the desired fields.

      • getComponentFieldsWhichShouldTriggerRefresh

        @NotNull
public java.util.List<MetafieldId> getComponentFieldsWhichShouldTriggerRefresh(@NotNull
                                                                                         java.lang.String inBaseEntity)
        Description copied from interface: IEntityCacheConfiguration
        Returns a list of component fields which always need to be refreshed. These are fields which contain hibernating entities as their constituent fields. For example, unitRouting is a component field (hibernate component Routing) of Unit entity which contains other entities like Routing points and Carrier Service. In such case if a field of the constituent entity is included as a cached field, say unitRouting.rtgPOD1.pointId, it does not come as part of update. the update contains a 'detached' Routing entity which only contains the gkeys of constituent entity fields. In such case it is better to re-fetch the cached object.
        Specified by:
        getComponentFieldsWhichShouldTriggerRefresh in interface IEntityCacheConfiguration
        Parameters:
        inBaseEntity - cached entity name
        Returns:
        list of component fields which should trigger refresh of cached object

      • shouldUpdateCauseRemovalOfCacheEntries

        public boolean shouldUpdateCauseRemovalOfCacheEntries(@NotNull
                                                      java.lang.String inCachedEntityName,
                                                      @NotNull
                                                      java.lang.String inUpdatedEntityName,
                                                      @NotNull
                                                      ValueHolder inUpdatedValues)
        Description copied from interface: IEntityCacheConfiguration
        Checks if the the entity update would cause removal of entry/entries from cache. If a related entity is being updated and cached entity has multiple relations to same foreign key entity (for example WorkInstructions can have multiple relations to Che, intended Che, nominated Che and so on), then all the cached entities related to updated entity will be removed irrespective of the relation CAUTION: Please note that there should be NO DB ACCESS or any other time consuming processing in this method as it is called for every update
        Specified by:
        shouldUpdateCauseRemovalOfCacheEntries in interface IEntityCacheConfiguration
        Parameters:
        inCachedEntityName - cached entity name
        inUpdatedEntityName - updated entity name
        inUpdatedValues - updated values
        Returns:
        true if the the entity update would cause removal of entry/entries from cache, false otherwise

      • addFieldToCache

        protected void addFieldToCache(@NotNull
                               MetafieldId inQualifiedMfid,
                               @NotNull
                               java.lang.String inCachedEntityName,
                               @NotNull
                               java.lang.String inEntityNameOfField)
        Adds the metafield to the cache. Intended to be used for customization the cache configuration.
        Parameters:
        inQualifiedMfid - the metafieldId qualified with respect to inCachedEntityName(the cached entity should be the left-most node of the field)
        inCachedEntityName - the name of the cached entity
        inEntityNameOfField - the name of the entity to which the 'unqualified' metafield belongs. For example, for qualified field 'ufvUnit.unitEquipment.eqEquipType.eqtypId', UnitFacilityVisit is the cached entity name and EquipType is the entityNameOfField

      • addComponentToCachedEntity

        protected void addComponentToCachedEntity(MetafieldId inComponentMetafieldId,
                                          java.util.List<MetafieldId> inConstituentFields,
                                          java.lang.String inCachedEntityName,
                                          java.lang.String inEntityNameOfField,
                                          boolean inRefreshOnChange)
        Add a new component to the cache
        Parameters:
        inComponentMetafieldId - the qualified component to be added
        inConstituentFields - the constituent fields of the component, they should be qualified by cached entity
        inCachedEntityName - cached entity name
        inEntityNameOfField - the entity to which component belongs
        inRefreshOnChange - should be true when the component has at least one field which is of type entity. for example IB carrier visit for component Unit Routing. In such case, the cached entity will be re-fetched from DB whenever a component field update is received.
